## Results

* What has been the business impact of this company so far?

In Q1 of 2018 the company was able to focus on widening their business model to cover all real assets. The emergence of this company and other companies in a similar scope
have introduced a new method of crowdfunding and fundraising. The utilization of distributed ledger technology allows for trust to be enforced in this domain. The company calls out
the current stock market to be a giant Ponzi scheme. The company is making it a personal mission for trust to be a main factor in the industry. 

* What are some of the core metrics that companies in this domain use to measure success? How is your company performing, based on these metrics?

Smartlands has tracked their progress as a company by providing a timeline of their main achievements. The company has also displayed the several financial media platforms
they have been featured in. The company has made an influence in the UK and, according to an article on crowdfundinsider.com, is currently working on making its service
available to the United States. Since their launch in 2017 the company has made progress towards widespread adoption in both UK and US markets. 

* How is your company performing relative to competitors in the same domain?

This company in terms of revenue has maintained an average revenue of 16M each quarter according to zoominfo.com and currently has 83 employees. Although the company is still in 
its start-up phase, it is performing pretty well compared to other startups in the same domain who are still in their developmental phases. 
Although it still has a while to go to compete with already established VC firms like Benchmark and Y Combinator. These companies have yet to transfer to the growing demand
for more distributed & trust business models. 


## Recommendations

* If you were to advise the company, what products or services would you suggest they offer? (This could be something that a competitor offers or use your imagination!)

I would suggest they offer a guide or coaching service similar to the way Y Combinator offers investment resources and mentoring services. 

* Why do you think that offering this product or service would benefit the company?

It would give them more of a competitive advantage than they already have. It will also help people unfamiliar with this new crowdfunding method transition to this new way 
of funding startups and real estate.  

* What technologies would this additional product or service utilize?

With the COVID rules and stipulations I would suggest using a virtual platform to communicate with customers such as Zoom. Their platform could also provide their own form of 
virtual communication. 

* Why are these technologies appropriate for your solution?

It would give the customer more freedom and independence to have control over crowdfunding their own start-ups or projects without feeling micromanaged by the firm. 
Many start-ups experience this micromanagement as Venture Capital seeks to gain a return on their investment.
